
Excercise1:

This is the first excercise and the task is how to run a .java file in your terminal or command prompt.
1. Download Java JDK at http://www.oracle.com/technetwork/java/javase/downloads/index.html (Links to an external site.)
2. Make sure you have the global java running environment by typing java under any folder in the terminal
3. Configure your Windows 10 environment by checking the web: https://www.mkyong.com/java/how-to-set-java_home-on-windows-10/ (Links to an external site.)
4. Download the two files from Database_Management_System repository: test1.java and the mysql-connector-java-5.1.32-bin.jar
5. Compile the test1.java by using the command:  java -cp .\mysql-connector-java-5.1.32-bin.jar test1.java
**To successfully run the commands above, you need to connect with the school network (WSU WIFI), or to use a machine on campus that connects to the same network (in any classroom that has computers)!
